<task id="installation-instructions-windows-server">
  <title><?oxy_comment_start author="Steven" timestamp="20170511T123327+0300" comment="Merged into &quot;eppo-installation-windows-server.dita&quot;. Moved to not_used folder."?>Configuring
    Windows Terminal Server<?oxy_comment_end?>
  </title>
  <shortdesc>Windows Terminal Server configuration procedure. </shortdesc>
  <taskbody>
    <steps>
      <step>
        <cmd>Install <ph keyref="product"/> on the server and make its shortcuts available to all
          users.</cmd>
      </step>
      <step>
        <cmd>If you need to run multiple instances of <ph keyref="product"/>, make sure you add the
            <userinput>-Dcom.oxygenxml.MultipleInstances=true</userinput> parameter in the
            <filepath>.bat</filepath> startup script.</cmd>
      </step>
      <step>
        <cmd>Make sure you allocate sufficient memory to <ph keyref="product"/> by adding the
            <codeph>-Xmx</codeph> parameter either in <xref
            href="set-parameters-for-application-launchers.dita#set-parameters-for-application-launchers"
            >the <i>.bat</i> startup script</xref>, or in <xref
            href="set-parameters-command-line-scripts.dita#set-parameters-command-line-scripts"
            >the <i>.vmoptions</i> configuration file</xref> (if you start it from an
          executable launcher).</cmd>
      </step>
    </steps>
  </taskbody>

</task>
